<p>This line is too long:</p>  <pre><code>btnNickname = TWeakObjectPtr&lt;UButton&gt;(Cast&lt;UButton&gt;(WidgetTree-&gt;FindWidget(FName(STRINGIFY(btnNickname)))); </code></pre>  <p>For a variable defined as:</p>  <pre><code>TWeakObjectPtr&lt;UButton&gt; btnNickname; </code></pre>  <p>I want to create macro for reduce the code:</p>  <pre><code>FIND_WIDGET(btnNickname); </code></pre>  <p>There are any way to do it?</p>  <p>I use this code now:</p>  <pre><code>#define FIND_WIDGET(TYPE, NAME) NAME = TWeakObjectPtr&lt;TYPE&gt;(Cast&lt;TYPE&gt;(WidgetTree-&gt;FindWidget(FName(STRINGIFY(NAME))))) </code></pre>  <p>But macro has two parameters. Can I get the pointer type from a <code>TWeakObjectPtr</code> variable? The <code>decltype</code> can give me type of variable, but not type of data of pointer.</p>  <p>Substance:</p>  <pre><code>#define FIND_WIDGET(NAME) NAME = TWeakObjectPtr&lt;decltype(*NAME)&gt;(Cast&lt;decltype(*NAME)&gt;(WidgetTree-&gt;FindWidget(FName(STRINGIFY(NAME))))) </code></pre>  <p>But this not works.</p>  <p>P.S. <a href="https://docs.unrealengine.com/latest/INT/API/Runtime/Core/UObject/TWeakObjectPtr/index.html" rel="nofollow"><code>TWeakObjectPtr</code></a> is smart pointer used in Unreal Engine 4.</p>